//- layout.jade
doctype html
html(lang="en")
  head
    block title
      title Watson Spoken Healthcare QA

    meta(charset="utf-8")
    meta(http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible", content="IE=edge")
    meta(name="viewport", content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1")

    link(rel="shortcut icon", href="/images/favicon.ico", type="image/x-icon")
    link(rel="icon", href="/images/favicon.ico", type="image/x-icon")
    link(rel="stylesheet", href="/css/watson-bootstrap-dark.css")
    link(rel="stylesheet", href="/css/browser-compatibility.css")
    link(rel="stylesheet", href="/css/style.css")
    block extrahead
  body
    div.container
      div.row
        div.col-lg-12
          div.row.top-nav
            div.col-lg-12
              a.left(href='http://www.tricedesigns.com/?p=4447') Learn more about this demo
              a.right(href='http://www.tricedesigns.com/about/') About
              a.right.fork(href='https://github.com/germanattanasio/IBMWatson-QA-Speech') Fork
          div.row.header(style='padding-bottom:0px;')
            div.avatar.img-container.col-lg-2.col-md-2.visible-lg.visible-md
              img(src='/images/watson.gif')
            div.col-lg-10.col-md-10
              h2 Watson Spoken Healthcare Question and Answer
              p The 
                a(href="http://www.ibm.com/smarterplanet/us/en/ibmwatson/developercloud/question-answer.html") IBM Watsonâ„¢ Question Answer (QA) service
                |  provides an API that give you the power of the IBM Watson cognitive computing system.
                |  With this service,
                | you can connect to Watson, pose questions in natural language, and receive responses
                | that you can use within your application.  The 
                a(href='http://www.ibm.com/smarterplanet/us/en/ibmwatson/developercloud/speech-to-text.html') IBM Watson Speech To Text
                |  service transcribes spoken language to text with low latency, and the 
                a(href='http://www.ibm.com/smarterplanet/us/en/ibmwatson/developercloud/text-to-speech.html') IBM Watson Text To Speech
                |  synthesizes natural sounding speeach from text.
              p In this sample, all three of these services have been hooked together to create a browser based system that enables the user ask questions in spoken language, Watson figures out the answer and speaks it back to the user.
    div.container
      block row-content
    div.container
      div.header.row
        div.col-lg-12
          h3 Disclaimer
          p The Watson API is incredibly powerful, but this sample is using the 
            a(href="http://www.ibm.com/smarterplanet/us/en/ibmwatson/developercloud/doc/qaapi/") sample public healthcare
            |  data set, which is only trained to answer 
            a(href="http://www.ibm.com/smarterplanet/us/en/ibmwatson/developercloud/doc/qaapi/#corpora") specific kinds of questions
            | . Check this out to see what a properly trained Watson instance can do for you. This demo requires getUserMedia 
            | for speech recognition and HTML5 audio for playing sounds. Parts of this demo may
            | not work if your browser does not support these features.
    div.container.footer
      div.row.text-center(style='margin:10px 0px 15px 0px;')
        a(href="/tos") Terms of Use
        |  | 
        a(href="http://www.ibm.com/privacy/us/en/") Privacy Policy
